Note: P2-D Q4 FFI Foundation Smoke Test — Unsafe External Call INSIDE Unsafe Block
Note:
Note: Per CEO Q4 amendment 2026-05-24, calling an unsafe External inside an
Note: Unsafe Block must compile cleanly. This file is the positive control
Note: for the unsafe-external-outside-block test.
Note:
Note: Expected output:
Note:   - Compilation: exit 0 (no FFI errors)
Note:   - Link/execute: behaves identically to a normal External

unsafe External Process called "raw_syscall_inside_test"
    that takes syscall_no as Integer
    returns Integer
    from library "c"
    convention c
    aliased as "syscall"

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Note: Wrap the unsafe-External call in an Unsafe Block — the active-rejection
    Note: check in lower_call_expression sees unsafe_depth > 0 and lets the call
    Note: through to the rest of the lowering pipeline.
    Let pid be 0
    Unsafe Block:
        Set pid to raw_syscall_inside_test(39)
    End Unsafe

    Note: Anything > 0 is a real PID; the OS guarantees PID 1 for init, so
    Note: any test environment will return a positive integer.
    If pid is greater than 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return 1
End Process
